value.0: What questions do you have about construction?

Territory ownership can be transferred by using the territory management menu. This is accessed by clicking on the territory flag. You'll receive a list of players currently online. Simply select who you want to give it to and confirm the transfer.

Be warned that all permission settings will be wiped and you will no longer have access to anything in the territory unless the new owner adds you to the permission list.

Only the territory owner may transfer ownership of the territory.

Razing your territory can be performed from the territory management menu. Access this by clicking the territory marker. You'll see an option to raze the territory and receive several confirmations before it actually happens.

Be warned that once razed, territories cannot be recovered. All materials put into them will be lost and can't be recovered. Be very careful!

Razing a territory may only be performed by the owner.

Building permissions can be changed at territory flags. These can only be adjusted by the owner of the territory. If the territory is the interior of a building, the permissions can be adjusted at the entrance or exit of the building.

These permissions include changing who is allowed to build, who can access item storage, and many other features. You should be very careful with whom you give access to, as they'll be able to make changes on your property without your permission.

New construction blueprints can be learned by purchasing the appropriate perks from the rest menu. You can access this menu by pressing 'R' or clicking the "Open Rest Menu" feat found on your hotbar.

Refer to the Perks Tutorial NPC for more information on perks.

Yes. Players can build houses, shops, or any other number of buildings. You have the option to choose what the outside of the building looks like and also the layout of the interior. There are also a number of variations in size. You'll have the option to preview all of these changes before you commit to building the structure too.

Structure limits dictate how many of each type of structure can be created in a single territory. This limit is defined by the type of territory flag you create.

The categories are as follows:

Vanity Limit: Structures which don't provide any sort of gameplay benefit beyond role-play.

Special Limit: Structures which provide a gameplay benefit such as item storage or increased HP/Mana regeneration.

Resource Limit: Structures designed to hold a specific type of resource. These are containers which only accept one type of item.

Building Limit: Structures with interiors such as houses and shops.


Once a category limit has been reached, no additional structures can be built unless an existing one is removed.

There is currently no limit to the number of territories you can own. However, we do ask that you be mindful of other players on the server. Don't just build anywhere or try to claim as much land as possible. 

Should there become a problem in the future we will impose limits on territory markers. For the time being, we want to give you as much creative freedom as possible.

Territory flags are locations which are claimed by players. They're the first thing you have to make before you can build anything else.

Territory flags have structure limits and a limited range. The location of the flag cannot overlap with the ownership of another player's territory.

You're allowed to build in most outside areas. Dungeons and interior areas like NPC shops are typically off-limits. If you're not allowed to build in an area you'll receive an error message when you use your structure tool.
Yes! Everything is completely persistent. You don't need to worry about losing your progress if the server resets. Simply build and enjoy - we'll take care of the heavy lifting.

You can create a construction site by using the feat "Structure Tool" found on your hot bar. If you removed it from your hot bar you can add it back by right clicking an empty button. Then go to Class Feats -> Fighter -> Structure Tool.

Once you've clicked the tool you'll want to select a location nearby. After clicking a location a menu will pop up with an option to create a construction site. Click this an the object will appear. 

Access the construction site by clicking on it. From here, click the "Select Blueprint" option and a new menu will appear. This menu will list all of the blueprints you can build. Pick one and your construction site will now be ready for building!

The construction system allows players to claim land and build structures like chairs, tables, campsites, and even entire buildings. You get full control over where things are placed, how they're positioned, and who has access to them.
